I'm pleased to announce the release of gerbv-2.5.0.  gerbv is the open 
source RS-274X and Excellon drill file viewer.  For more information on 
gerbv, visit

   http://gerbv.gpleda.org
   http://www.sourceforge.net/projects/gerbv

Many thanks to the users who submitted bug reports and patches, especially
Stefan Tauner for his work on menu cleanup and adding keyboard accelerators
for all commands.

========================================================================
Release Notes for gerbv-2.5.0
========================================================================
The following is a summary of the changes which went into gerbv-2.5.0.
For a complete list of changes, refer to ChangeLog.

New features:
	- menu cleanup and add persistent keyboard accelerators for all
		commands (thanks to Stefan Tauner)
	- allow for toggling the visibility of the sidebar and toolbar
		(patch by Stefan Tauner)

Bug fixes and improvements:
	- fix drill parsing bug when INCH command is followed by whitespace
	- unselect items on hidden layers
	- fix bug when exporting outline macros
	- fix handling of whitespace within RS274X commands
	- fix GDK rendering of macro 22 elements with negative coordinates
	- fix tooltip on modify layer button
	- fix the example programs for using libgerbv
	- improve drill file type guesser
	- pixel-align as many Cairo operations as possible (~10% speedup)
	- fix segfault in drill parser
	- fix segfault in pick-and-place parser
	- increase max zoom 4x to improve measurement accuracy

